comments: Sengun (HOU) establishes himself in O'Neale's (BKN) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Claxton (BKN) brings his arm toward Green's (HOU) path and marginal arm contact occurs during Green drive.
Sengun (HOU) jumps somewhat towards Claxton (BKN) off ball and marginal body contact occurs to Claxton's side as he gathers the pass in the lane.
Smith Jr. (HOU) places his slightly extended arm against Claxton's (BKN) front and marginal body contact occurs during layup attempt.
Claxton (BKN) and Sengun (HOU) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Dinwiddie (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Bridges (BKN) and Sengun (HOU) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball in the post.
Claxton (BKN) is firming up as he absorbs the contact the after Sengun's (HOU) gather and marginal body contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Johnson (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
O'Neale (BKN) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.

Sengun (HOU) and Bridges (BKN) come together underneath the basket and marginal contact occurs to Bridges' head as they get briefly engage while pursuing the loose ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Sengun (HOU) extends his arm underneath the basket and incidental head contact occurs to O"Neale (BKN) as they pursue the loose ball.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Claxton (BKN) lightly brushes Sengun' (HOU) arm during his upward shooting motion, as Johnson (BKN) dislodges his shot attempt at the basket.
O'Neale (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from Sengun (HOU) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Sengun (HOU) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly given to BKN.
